# geniro-app — environment (all optional)
#
# geniro-app is local-first and needs no API keys or cloud config. The Electron
# shell sets the daemon's env automatically when it spawns it; the vars below
# are only useful for running the daemon standalone (`pnpm daemon:dev`).
#
# Nothing auto-loads this file — the daemon reads process.env directly. Export
# the vars, prefix them inline, or pass them via Node's `--env-file=.env`.
#
# Secrets are NEVER stored here or in any file — user credentials live in the
# macOS Keychain only.

# Daemon data directory (holds the SQLite db `geniro.db` + the `daemon.json`
# pidfile). Default: ~/.geniro
# GENIRO_USER_DATA=

# Daemon preferred loopback port (always bound on 127.0.0.1; falls back to a
# free port if this one is taken). Default: 47615
# GENIRO_PORT=
